\title{Implied Weighting Command}
\description{
An \link[R6:R6Class]{R6} class that configures standard implied weighting in
\pkg{nitro}.

Implied weighting (Goloboff, 1993) down-weights homoplastic characters
using a concavity function controlled by a constant \emph{k}. Lower values of
\emph{k} apply stronger down-weighting. This wraps the TNT \code{piwe} command.

For extended implied weighting (where each character receives an
independent concavity constant), see \link{ExtendedImpliedWeightingCommand}.
In practice, both are most conveniently configured together via
\code{\link[=set_weighting]{set_weighting()}}.
}
